   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can deactivate business units to make them unavailable for selection while creating projects and user accounts. Also, a deactivated business unit is unavailable to create a sub-level business unit.</context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the module menu, click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Administration</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol>page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the navigation pane, expand<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Functional Configurations</uicontrol>, and then click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Business Unit</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">BUSINESS UNIT</uicontrol> list pageis displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the required business unit, and then click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Edit</uicontrol>.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Clear the<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Is Active</uicontrol> check box.</cmd>
